summary: P L E A S E. Aziraphale stroking his belly, smiling over at Crowley who's insisting on doing some bit of housework himself, and...
question: P L E A S E. Aziraphale stroking his belly, smiling over at Crowley who's insisting on doing some bit of housework himself, and dreamily saying he HOPES the baby has Crowley's eyes?? And Crowley dying, because on the one hand, very inconvenient to deal with, he wouldn't wish his eyes on anyone, but on the other hand, he's so disarmed by how much Aziraphale loves him and sees the beauty in him.
answer: Crowley absolutely falls apart. Aziraphale is just sitting at his desk in the bookshop and he’s about tidying shelves and the two had been lightly bickering because “No, dear boy, I have a system-“ “Well, your system is ridiculous to anyone with eyes.” And somehow this leads to Aziraphale’s sincere revelation that he wants the child to be blessed (his words) with Crowley’s eyes. Crowley just freezes and turns to look at Aziraphale, the angel just sitting there, fucking oblivious to the bomb he just dropped. He’s drinking cocoa, for somebody’s sake! And he’s put his hand on his stomach and he’s completely ignoring Crowley, his attention now on the child as he tells them how he would love them regardless, but he really does think they’d be lovely with Crowley’s yellow eyes and the demon is ready to explode over how torn he feels.
